# Walkthrough: Unified UI & Task Card Overhaul

We have successfully completed a comprehensive UI refactoring of the Sprint Relay application, moving to a premium, high-contrast light-mode aesthetic centered around a new navy blue accent (`#1D3557`).

## Key Changes

### 1. Branding & Theme
- **Global Accent Update**: Replaced all purple/indigo branding with a professional navy blue (`#1D3557`) in [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/globals.css).
- **Light Mode First**: Optimized all components for a crisp, high-contrast light-mode experience.

### 2. Unified TaskCard Component
- **Shared Component**: Created [TaskCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/TaskCard.tsx) to handle all task displays across the application, replacing fragmented local implementations and the legacy `DraggableTaskCard`.
- **Enhanced Metadata**: Added clear, readable tags for **Module** (navy) and **Screen** (gray), allowing for a quicker overview of task context.
- **Refined Typography**: Balanced the task title weight from heavy black to a professional bold for better visual comfort.
- **Clean Interface**: Removed the redundant "Sync Squad" button from individual cards to reduce clutter.

### 3. Centralized Status System
- **[status-utils.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/status-utils.tsx)**: Consolidated all status badge and priority dot logic into a single utility file.
- **High-Contrast Badges**: Redesigned all status indicators for maximum readability in light mode.

### 4. View Refactoring
- Refactored **Daily Meeting**, **Next Sprint Planning**, **Daily Recap**, **Personnel Overview**, and **Task Overview** to use the new unified components and theme.
- Fixed various build errors and legacy dark-theme artifacts.

